history.content:
No, you must go to the lab you're registered for due to space constraints.

Official policy this semester (won't change much or at all next semester): "Labs for this class are not open section, you must go to your assigned lab section unless you have extenuating circumstances. If these circumstances do occur, show up to the lab section you would like to go to. It is at the discretion of the lab TA whether or not to let you into their section if you are not officially enrolled."

children.subject: only if the GSI for that lab says it is OK
Should waitlisted students go to the section they tried to enroll in?

history.content:
Open spots are decreasing like my hopes for getting into the section I want

I also want to be able to eat lunch at 12 and dinner at 6 like a normal person... or is that just a non-Californian thing?!

So the best section for my class schedule (and sleep schedule) is Thursday 2-5, but all spots in that section are currently taken and I have no idea what position I am on the waitlist.

With that said is it possible, like discussion, to just go to any 16A lab we want regardless of whether we're officially enrolled?
